# nwPlus Portal v2 - Cursor Rules

## Design System & Styling

### Color Tokens
**ALWAYS use Figma-derived color tokens from our custom design system.**

Our color tokens use a double-prefix naming convention:
- Text colors: `text-text-primary`, `text-text-secondary`, `text-text-error`, `text-text-accent`
- Background colors: `bg-bg-main`, `bg-bg-pane-container`, `bg-bg-button-primary`, `bg-bg-button-secondary`
- Border colors: `border-border-subtle`, `border-border-active`, `border-border-danger`, `border-border-accent`

The double prefix (e.g., `text-text-*`) is INTENTIONAL - it's how Tailwind v4 generates utilities from our `--color-text-*` theme tokens.

### Examples of CORRECT usage:
```tsx
<h1 className="text-text-primary">Heading</h1>
<p className="text-text-secondary">Description</p>
<div className="bg-bg-pane-container border border-border-subtle">...</div>
<button className="bg-bg-button-primary text-text-primary">Submit</button>
```

### NEVER use:
❌ Default Tailwind colors: `bg-gray-900`, `text-white`, `border-slate-200`
❌ shadcn defaults: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-primary`


Reference: See `src/styles.css` (`@theme inline` section) for complete token list.